Introduction

This is a digest of results from a battery of web accessibility tests.

Ten different tools (Alfa, Axe, Continuum, Equal Access, HTML CodeSniffer, Nu Html Checker, QualWeb, Tenon, Testaro, and WAVE) tested the web page of Steven Bradford (D) at https://sd35.senate.ca.gov/ to check its compliance with various rules. There were a total of about 1350 rules, classified into about 250 accessibility issues.

The results were interpreted to yield an aggregate score of 3106, where 0 would be perfect.

Total score

The total score is the sum of five components.

Score summary
ComponentScoreDescription
total3106Sum of the component scores
issue2342Severity and number of reported defects
tool453Tool-by-tool defect ratings
prevention300Failed attempts by tools to test the page
log11Browser warnings about the page
latency0Abnormal delay in page responses

Issue scores

The score of an issue depends on the severity (user impact and certainty) of the issue and on how many instances were reported (by one or more tools).

Itemized issues

The reported rule violations are itemized below, issue by issue. Additional details can be inspected in the complete report at the end of this page.

Count of instances: 3

Complaint specifics
